Tips on how to create the perfect stripes, tips below 👇 
Also letting the cat out of the bag, I’m planning on filming my first YouTube video on this topic in October 🎉 
A full how to tutorial type of video ( been putting off YouTube forever cause it scares me 😂) anyways ….

⭐️ stripe tips ⭐️ 
Before ANYTHING else make sure your layers are as straight as you can get them! This helps so much when you’re scraping off your stripes. If your cake sides are all uneven, you end up scraping away more buttercream from one area then the other 😑 which is so so hard to fix! 

⭐️ pipe the stripes one at a time instead of icing the whole cake and having to scrape off more then half of the buttercream. In my opinion it creates twice as much work and mess. 

⭐️ let it chill in your freezer for 15 mins or until you can touch the buttercream and it doesn’t come off in your finger. Fill in your colours and start scraping right away, since the cake is chilled you don’t want to let the new buttercream sit to long or it becomes harder to move around the cake 

⭐️ once you are happy with your stripes, run your cake comb under hot water and go around slowly in one motion 🤗 
Let me know below if this help 😘

It’s been one of those days where you want to throw a cake at a wall (not going to lie, a small part of me always wants to throw a cake at the wall but usually not out of frustration 😂) 

So mini rant, nothing is going right 😑 editing software stopped working, dropped a bottle of food colouring on the floor, washing machine stopped working and Amber ( 🐕) decided to ditch me all day and hang out with Adam (that one hurt the most 😂) 

Ok end of rant 😂 sometimes I just need to get it off my chest, now back to work and time to find a new editing software and google how to fix a washing machine 😜 love you, and hope you’re having a better day !!!

Tools every baker needs 🤗 list below 👇 
I get this question a lot and in my opinion you don’t need to go out a buy a ton of tools (I did this when I first started and I still have tools and molds I haven’t used 😂) 

MUST HAVE TOOLS 
⭐️ good turntable, don’t go cheap here because if you’re going to start a cake business you’ll use this everyday ! My go to one is Ateco #615 

⭐️ Basic piping tip set 
My go to piping tips are Ateco # 860, 869 (French star tips) 
# 120 # 124 

Ateco circle piping tips 
# 807 # 804 # 803 
Ateco has some great piping kits I would start there 

⭐️ cake combs 
I would recommend @sweet_escape001 
They have a cake comb that has a straight edge and pinstripes ( my most used) I would also recommend getting one texture cake comb because the possibilities are gorgeous and endless 

Lastly non slip mat under the turntable, you can get these from the dollar store 

Let me know below if you want more post like these 🤗
